  "prompt": "Why do people upload files to torrents?",
  "response": "People upload files to torrents for various reasons:\n\n1. File sharing\n- Distribute large files efficiently\n- Share open-source software\n- Share public domain content\n- Share legally obtained media\n\n2. Cost effectiveness\n- Reduces bandwidth costs\n- Distributes file transfer load across multiple users\n- Enables sharing of large files without expensive hosting\n\n3. Accessibility\n- Allows global file distribution\n- Provides access to hard-to-find content\n- Enables sharing of content that might be geographically restricted\n\n4. Community support\n- Contributing to online file-sharing communities\n- Helping others access content\n- Maintaining availability of specific files\n\n5. Preservation\n- Archiving content that might otherwise disappear\n- Ensuring long-term availability of files\n\n6. Personal motivation\n- Sharing personal content\n- Supporting specific interests or subcultures\n\nWhile torrents can be used legally, they are sometimes also used to share copyrighted material without permission, which is illegal in many jurisdictions.",
